1
00:00:01,080 --> 00:00:03,830
Hey, all you viewers out there!

2
00:00:03,830 --> 00:00:07,130
When you're watchin' Fairy Tail, make 
sure to keep the room nice and bright,

3
00:00:07,130 --> 00:00:09,240
and sit back from the screen, 'kay?

4
00:00:10,610 --> 00:00:12,820
Previously on Fairy Tail!

5
00:00:13,120 --> 00:00:15,860
Oh, no! The Council is angry!

6
00:00:15,860 --> 00:00:19,490
Well of course they'd be angry after 
we keep running amuck all the time.

7
00:00:19,490 --> 00:00:21,900
Thank you very much...

8
00:00:21,900 --> 00:00:24,420
The master has been called before the Council!

9
00:00:24,420 --> 00:00:25,100
What'll we do?

10
00:00:25,100 --> 00:00:26,930
Thank you very much!

11
00:00:26,930 --> 00:00:29,310
And wait... Who are you?

12
00:00:49,220 --> 00:00:53,630
It'll be all right! I'll yell it out countless times.

13
00:00:53,630 --> 00:00:58,700
I believe your every tomorrow will be shining.

14
00:00:58,700 --> 00:01:01,050
The intersection of all people

15
00:01:01,050 --> 00:01:03,660
whose dreams have come true is one point:

16
00:01:03,660 --> 00:01:08,290
Never giving up.  And that's why we're not gonna lose!

17
00:01:08,290 --> 00:01:13,470
When it seems like you'll be blown away by the headwinds,

18
00:01:13,470 --> 00:01:15,620
grasp this hand, try to take a chance.

19
00:01:15,620 --> 00:01:18,890
Because you're not alone anymore, got it?

20
00:01:22,010 --> 00:01:24,000
Go forward, more and more!

21
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:26,520
Don't give up on your awesome dream!

22
00:01:26,520 --> 00:01:27,780
That's right, don't cry!

23
00:01:27,780 --> 00:01:29,250
Move on, my way!

24
00:01:29,250 --> 00:01:31,630
Now, with the light shining down upon you.

25
00:01:31,630 --> 00:01:33,710
Don't even think about something like giving up!

26
00:01:33,710 --> 00:01:36,140
Even if you trade being hurt again for strength.

27
00:01:36,140 --> 00:01:41,630
Your eyes, always looking straight ahead,

28
00:01:41,630 --> 00:01:45,910
can surely see the light!

29
00:02:11,270 --> 00:02:13,150
Um... Makarov, sir?

30
00:02:13,150 --> 00:02:14,070
Yes?

31
00:02:14,370 --> 00:02:19,150
We are in the middle of the trial... I 
presume you are not sleeping, correct?

32
00:02:19,530 --> 00:02:21,460
But of course not!

33
00:02:26,320 --> 00:02:28,810
Phantom Lord has been disbanded.

34
00:02:28,810 --> 00:02:31,680
And Jose has been stripped of his 
place among the 10 Wizard Saints.

35
00:02:31,680 --> 00:02:34,170
So far, that's as I expected.

36
00:02:34,590 --> 00:02:37,910
But to judge Fairy Tail 
as completely "innocent?"

37
00:02:37,910 --> 00:02:40,250
I wouldn't have expected that.

38
00:02:40,250 --> 00:02:42,270
You should be grateful, Macky.

39
00:02:42,270 --> 00:02:44,180
I argued on your behalf, you know.

40
00:02:44,480 --> 00:02:46,780
I'm in your debt, Yaji.

41
00:02:46,780 --> 00:02:50,500
When the guild's fixed up, 
come over for a visit.

42
00:02:50,500 --> 00:02:52,570
I'll treat you to some ramen.

43
00:02:52,570 --> 00:02:56,690
I'd like a Fairy Ramen with 12 pork slices.

44
00:02:56,690 --> 00:02:59,200
12 slices is a bit much, you think?

45
00:02:59,200 --> 00:03:04,030
Remember you violated the ban on 
inter-guild conflict in Paragraph 4!

46
00:03:04,030 --> 00:03:05,340
Oh, fine!

47
00:03:05,340 --> 00:03:08,560
I'll put in 20 or 30 slices if you want!

48
00:03:08,560 --> 00:03:10,250
12 pork slices.

49
00:03:15,480 --> 00:03:19,020
Macky... Don't push yourself.

50
00:03:19,730 --> 00:03:22,840
We're no longer young.

51
00:03:24,540 --> 00:03:26,620
You still haven't forgotten, yes?

52
00:03:26,620 --> 00:03:27,590
About what?

53
00:03:27,590 --> 00:03:29,700
About Rob.

54
00:03:29,700 --> 00:03:33,020
Rob... Rob, huh?

55
00:03:33,620 --> 00:03:37,420
Me and you and Poluchka...

56
00:03:37,420 --> 00:03:39,300
And Rob too...

57
00:03:39,300 --> 00:03:42,070
We were all so young.

58
00:03:42,070 --> 00:03:46,350
We overdid it, but every day sure was a fun.

59
00:03:46,350 --> 00:03:56,670
Then Rob quit Fairy Tail... Erza 
tells me stories once in a while.

60
00:03:57,370 --> 00:04:03,590
Lately many people are of the opinion that 
Fairy Tail has gone too far too often.

61
00:04:04,310 --> 00:04:09,430
Indeed, Michello and Org have 
requested you be disbanded.

62
00:04:09,780 --> 00:04:14,480
At this rate you will be facing 
serious punishment, Macky.

63
00:04:15,150 --> 00:04:18,050
Dead, you're no good to anybody.

64
00:04:18,650 --> 00:04:20,730
Like Rob...

65
00:04:20,730 --> 00:04:25,380
Macky, hurry up and retire. 
For the sake of your health.

66
00:04:29,840 --> 00:04:32,130
Next Generation!

67
00:04:34,990 --> 00:04:40,110
Everyone! You can all take
jobs again starting today!

68
00:04:40,110 --> 00:04:43,980
It's just a temporary counter, 
but do all the jobs you can!

69
00:04:45,930 --> 00:04:48,050
What's with them?

70
00:04:48,430 --> 00:04:52,230
Usually they're just hanging 
around not taking any jobs.

71
00:04:53,320 --> 00:04:55,670
Oh, yeah, I haven't seen Loke around...

72
00:04:55,670 --> 00:05:00,080
I see you've finally fallen for 
Loke's magic touch then, Lucy...

73
00:05:00,080 --> 00:05:01,390
That's not it!

74
00:05:01,390 --> 00:05:05,870
I just heard that he found my 
keys, so I wanted to thank him.

75
00:05:05,870 --> 00:05:08,650
Sure. I'll tell him if I see him around.

76
00:05:08,650 --> 00:05:11,370
By the way, weren't your Spirits angry?

77
00:05:11,370 --> 00:05:13,020
About you dropping your keys?

78
00:05:14,690 --> 00:05:18,880
Oh, it wasn't anything enough for 
them to get that mad about...

79
00:05:18,880 --> 00:05:22,050
I told you not to drop it, girl!

80
00:05:24,580 --> 00:05:27,780
Just remembering makes my butt sting...

81
00:05:27,780 --> 00:05:28,680
Oh, my...

82
00:05:29,850 --> 00:05:31,240
Shall I chill it for you?

83
00:05:31,240 --> 00:05:33,100
I don't need innuendo-style sexual harassment.

84
00:05:33,400 --> 00:05:35,710
Lucy, let me see your bright red butt!

85
00:05:35,710 --> 00:05:37,520
And no overt sexual harassment either!

86
00:05:38,640 --> 00:05:41,560
I wonder what she'll look like 
if I make it sting even more!

87
00:05:41,560 --> 00:05:43,190
And you're just the devil!

88
00:05:44,410 --> 00:05:46,150
Try saying that again!

89
00:05:51,290 --> 00:05:52,580
Erza?

90
00:05:52,840 --> 00:05:56,120
This time I'll tell you straight out.

91
00:05:56,120 --> 00:05:59,370
We don't need weaklings in this guild!

92
00:05:59,370 --> 00:06:01,630
You guys are pitiful.

93
00:06:01,630 --> 00:06:04,100
Getting humiliated by Phantom like that...

94
00:06:04,100 --> 00:06:06,910
And wait, I don't even know your names.

95
00:06:08,280 --> 00:06:14,000
And you there, the main culprit, the debutant 
Celestial Spirit user... It was your fault.

96
00:06:14,000 --> 00:06:14,850
Laxus!

97
00:06:15,150 --> 00:06:17,040
It's all over now.

98
00:06:17,040 --> 00:06:20,470
No one has been talking 
about who to blame for it.

99
00:06:20,470 --> 00:06:23,110
You have no right to say anything 
when you didn't even help us fight!

100
00:06:23,410 --> 00:06:25,320
That's what the master says.

101
00:06:25,320 --> 00:06:28,740
Well, yeah! It had nothing to do with me!

102
00:06:29,040 --> 00:06:33,160
Although if I had been there, you 
wouldn't have had all that trouble.

103
00:06:33,860 --> 00:06:34,870
Why, you...

104
00:06:34,870 --> 00:06:36,370
Hold it right there!

105
00:06:35,260 --> 00:06:36,330
Natsu!

106
00:06:41,710 --> 00:06:44,230
Laxus! Fight me!

107
00:06:44,230 --> 00:06:46,020
You heartless bastard!

108
00:06:47,280 --> 00:06:50,630
What kind of fight would it be 
when you can't even catch me?

109
00:06:50,630 --> 00:06:54,400
When I inherit the guild, I'll 
get rid of all the weaklings.

110
00:06:54,890 --> 00:06:57,840
As well as anyone who stands against me!

111
00:06:57,840 --> 00:07:00,080
I'll make the ultimate guild!

112
00:07:00,080 --> 00:07:03,230
The strongest guild in history 
that no one can look down upon!

113
00:07:10,460 --> 00:07:13,790
Inherit? What nonsense is he talking about?

114
00:07:13,790 --> 00:07:15,830
It's not nonsense.

115
00:07:15,830 --> 00:07:19,500
Laxus is the master's grandson, you see.

116
00:07:22,460 --> 00:07:28,410
So when Master retires, the chances that 
Laxus becomes the next master are quite high.

117
00:07:28,410 --> 00:07:30,090
B-But...

118
00:07:30,360 --> 00:07:37,610
I'd be against someone becoming the master 
who thinks that way about his allies.

119
00:07:37,610 --> 00:07:42,660
The rumor is that's why he 
hasn't been able to retire.

120
00:07:42,660 --> 00:07:44,100
Is that it?

121
00:07:44,100 --> 00:07:46,120
That jerk!

122
00:07:46,120 --> 00:07:49,280
Enough. You'll just tire 
yourself out dealing with him.

123
00:07:49,280 --> 00:07:52,280
Anyway, what do you think? Want to go do a job?

124
00:07:53,500 --> 00:07:56,320
Together with Gray and Lucy, of course.

125
00:07:56,320 --> 00:07:57,280
What?

126
00:07:57,280 --> 00:07:58,890
Gray, your clothes...

127
00:07:59,410 --> 00:08:03,410
I have a sense that we've been together 
ever since the Eisenwald incident.

128
00:08:03,670 --> 00:08:07,280
<i>Now</i> you get a "sense" like that?

129
00:08:07,280 --> 00:08:10,050
We all thought it was pretty obvious.

130
00:08:10,050 --> 00:08:12,320
She never stopped to think about it herself?

131
00:08:12,320 --> 00:08:14,100
That's Erza for you.

132
00:08:14,100 --> 00:08:16,340
Let's form a team now.

133
00:08:16,340 --> 00:08:19,890
With the four of us. Or 
five, if you count Happy.

134
00:08:24,090 --> 00:08:27,420
But do you really want someone like me?

135
00:08:27,420 --> 00:08:28,870
Not someone like you...

136
00:08:29,970 --> 00:08:31,960
Someone that <i>is</i> you, Lucy!

137
00:08:31,960 --> 00:08:32,780
Aye!

138
00:08:33,050 --> 00:08:36,500
Without you, things just 
wouldn't fit right, you know?

139
00:08:40,550 --> 00:08:44,250
Looks like Fairy Tail's strongest 
team is official now.

140
00:08:44,250 --> 00:08:45,290
Good for them.

141
00:08:45,290 --> 00:08:47,500
And wait, Lucy's the strongest?

142
00:08:47,500 --> 00:08:50,880
If I was up against Aquarius, 
I couldn't win either.

143
00:08:50,880 --> 00:08:52,640
And her straight-man act is amazing!

144
00:08:52,640 --> 00:08:54,220
The "strongest" in a lot of different ways.

145
00:08:54,220 --> 00:08:56,020
W-With <i>him</i>?

146
00:08:56,020 --> 00:08:57,310
Got a problem?

147
00:08:57,310 --> 00:08:59,420
No, never happier!

148
00:08:59,420 --> 00:09:01,050
Let's hurry and do a job.

149
00:09:01,050 --> 00:09:04,380
We'll take down the Magic Sect operating in 
the shadows of the castle town of Lupinus!

150
00:09:04,380 --> 00:09:05,300
Let's go!

151
00:09:14,140 --> 00:09:16,160
Retire, huh?

152
00:09:17,830 --> 00:09:20,160
The guild's being remade.

153
00:09:20,160 --> 00:09:23,660
So then the master should also 
pass to the next generation.

154
00:09:23,910 --> 00:09:25,640
Laxus...

155
00:09:25,640 --> 00:09:28,590
His attitude has some big problems.

156
00:09:29,050 --> 00:09:30,770
Mystogan...

157
00:09:30,770 --> 00:09:33,840
He's basically a poster-boy 
for lack of communication.

158
00:09:35,180 --> 00:09:39,090
And then there's Erza, but 
she's still too young...

159
00:09:39,090 --> 00:09:42,610
Master? You're up there?

160
00:09:43,720 --> 00:09:46,120
It looks like they've gone and done it again.

161
00:09:47,500 --> 00:09:51,480
It seems like Erza and her team 
destroyed half a city while on a job.

162
00:09:53,850 --> 00:09:58,510
The Council has requested you submit 
a written explanation immediately!

163
00:09:59,900 --> 00:10:01,410
Huh? Master, what's the matter?

164
00:10:01,710 --> 00:10:05,410
Retire? No frickin' way!

165
00:10:07,800 --> 00:10:10,630
Oh? You don't seem so well, Lucy.

166
00:10:10,630 --> 00:10:11,580
What's the matter?

167
00:10:11,580 --> 00:10:14,250
The job at Lupinus from earlier.

168
00:10:15,000 --> 00:10:18,530
Sheesh... Natsu spewed fire everywhere...

169
00:10:18,530 --> 00:10:20,670
Gray froze everything...

170
00:10:20,670 --> 00:10:22,370
And Erza...

171
00:10:23,060 --> 00:10:25,030
Erza especially!

172
00:10:25,030 --> 00:10:26,680
Hey, Lucy... You okay?

173
00:10:27,020 --> 00:10:33,360
Anyway, with all the destruction, most 
of our reward goes to pay reparations!

174
00:10:33,750 --> 00:10:37,330
At this rate, I won't be able 
to pay this month's rent!

175
00:10:37,330 --> 00:10:41,920
Then why don't I recommend 
a perfect job for you?

176
00:10:41,920 --> 00:10:46,330
It's right up your alley, Lucy, and there's 
no need to worry about destroying anything!

177
00:10:49,320 --> 00:10:51,190
And so...

178
00:10:53,320 --> 00:10:56,630
Onibas?  The city from the lullaby incident.

179
00:10:56,630 --> 00:10:58,970
Natsu, we're here.

180
00:10:59,290 --> 00:11:00,330
It's no use...

181
00:11:00,330 --> 00:11:06,600
So it's a request for us to use our magic to 
attract lots of people to see a play, right?

182
00:11:06,900 --> 00:11:08,300
Exactly.

183
00:11:08,300 --> 00:11:09,490
Sounds fun, right?

184
00:11:09,490 --> 00:11:14,600
Natsu can shoot fire, and you two can put on a show
with your Creation Magic and her Requipping!

185
00:11:14,600 --> 00:11:17,230
Then I'll move everyone's 
hearts with Lyra's singing.

186
00:11:17,230 --> 00:11:18,990
It'll be a wonderful 
performance, don't you think?

187
00:11:19,290 --> 00:11:22,810
If I ever finish my novel, I 
hope it gets turned into a play.

188
00:11:22,810 --> 00:11:26,900
Right! This is a great opportunity 
to study staging a play!

189
00:11:30,910 --> 00:11:32,500
It's a pretty nice place.

190
00:11:32,850 --> 00:11:33,710
Let's go!

191
00:11:33,710 --> 00:11:35,670
Um...

192
00:11:36,040 --> 00:11:38,880
You are the people from Fairy Tail, yes?

193
00:11:39,110 --> 00:11:39,980
Yes!

194
00:11:39,980 --> 00:11:43,600
Thank you very much for accepting my request!

195
00:11:43,600 --> 00:11:45,890
Sure! Just leave the stage work to us!

196
00:11:45,890 --> 00:11:47,750
About that...

197
00:11:48,100 --> 00:11:51,430
We have a bit of a problem...

198
00:12:00,750 --> 00:12:04,070
What? The actors have all run out on you?

199
00:12:04,370 --> 00:12:06,920
That is correct. Thank you very much.

200
00:12:06,920 --> 00:12:07,870
Thanks for what?

201
00:12:08,170 --> 00:12:11,070
My plays have been more and more unpopular.

202
00:12:11,070 --> 00:12:16,830
So now, the actors are ashamed 
to be in my productions!

203
00:12:16,830 --> 00:12:21,010
Even my wife tired of me 
chasing my dream and left me!

204
00:12:21,010 --> 00:12:25,200
This was my last chance!

205
00:12:25,200 --> 00:12:27,650
Thank you so very much!

206
00:12:27,650 --> 00:12:29,510
You don't get this "thanking" thing, do you?

207
00:12:29,800 --> 00:12:32,720
Anyway, the play is canceled!

208
00:12:32,720 --> 00:12:34,780
Thank you very much!

209
00:12:34,780 --> 00:12:37,090
I figured it was something, but this?

210
00:12:38,760 --> 00:12:42,320
If you need actors, then 
you've got some right here!

211
00:12:42,760 --> 00:12:44,780
S-She's shining!

212
00:12:47,530 --> 00:12:49,280
She's doing vocal exercises!

213
00:12:49,500 --> 00:12:52,700
Well, that does sound kind of fun.

214
00:12:52,700 --> 00:12:53,720
Really?

215
00:12:53,720 --> 00:12:54,550
Aye!

216
00:12:54,550 --> 00:12:57,460
We won't let your dream end here!

217
00:12:58,430 --> 00:13:01,150
You're so...

218
00:13:01,150 --> 00:13:03,660
Well, might as well let them give it a shot.

219
00:13:03,660 --> 00:13:05,320
Damn amateurs.

220
00:13:05,320 --> 00:13:07,470
<i>Now</i> you don't thank us?

221
00:13:08,570 --> 00:13:10,970
We have one week until opening.

222
00:13:12,190 --> 00:13:13,970
I am Fredrick!

223
00:13:13,970 --> 00:13:16,640
And I have come to save the Princess!

224
00:13:16,640 --> 00:13:19,580
Wow, Erza! You've got quite the stage presence!

225
00:13:19,580 --> 00:13:21,900
She's really gotten into the role.

226
00:13:21,900 --> 00:13:23,290
I won't lose to her!

227
00:13:23,290 --> 00:13:24,110
Yeah.

228
00:13:24,110 --> 00:13:25,910
Aye, sir!

229
00:13:27,460 --> 00:13:35,730
After that, when we weren't practicing, we were 
handing out fliers and constructing the set...

230
00:13:35,730 --> 00:13:38,790
Remembering all the lines was pretty tough.

231
00:13:38,790 --> 00:13:43,710
But in the end, we were all in the spirit 
of it and having more fun than ever.

232
00:13:44,010 --> 00:13:47,420
Some fans are here to see 
you, thank you very much.

233
00:13:47,420 --> 00:13:48,510
Fans?

234
00:13:48,810 --> 00:13:49,760
Yo!

235
00:13:51,660 --> 00:13:53,680
I don't even know where to start!

236
00:13:53,980 --> 00:13:56,420
It's almost time for the debut 
performance. Break a leg!

237
00:13:56,420 --> 00:13:58,640
It's been so long since I've seen a play!

238
00:13:58,640 --> 00:14:00,940
I appreciate the invitation, Macky.

239
00:14:00,940 --> 00:14:03,410
Long time no see! How've you been?

240
00:14:03,410 --> 00:14:05,120
I came to heckle you.

241
00:14:05,120 --> 00:14:05,820
Meat!

242
00:14:06,120 --> 00:14:09,240
And wait, what are <i>you</i> doing 
here, fake Salamander!

243
00:14:09,240 --> 00:14:10,810
It's been a while, Micheal.

244
00:14:10,810 --> 00:14:12,180
It's Bora!

245
00:14:12,180 --> 00:14:18,330
After my heart was hit with your fiery fist, 
I've given up forcibly scouting for pin-up girls!

246
00:14:19,580 --> 00:14:22,290
Was that what happened again?

247
00:14:23,810 --> 00:14:25,510
What did you think it was?

248
00:14:25,510 --> 00:14:26,790
Uh, well...

249
00:14:26,790 --> 00:14:28,970
Lucy was thinking of naughty things!

250
00:14:29,200 --> 00:14:31,280
Madame, I'll be rooting for you!

251
00:14:31,280 --> 00:14:32,910
Sorry about having you come all this way.

252
00:14:33,390 --> 00:14:34,180
So hard!

253
00:14:34,870 --> 00:14:36,670
Aren't you from Galuna Island?

254
00:14:36,670 --> 00:14:37,460
I'm Lulu!

255
00:14:37,460 --> 00:14:39,740
Thanks again for back then.

256
00:14:40,630 --> 00:14:43,110
And aren't you from Phantom?

257
00:14:43,110 --> 00:14:46,320
I was also captivated by his power!

258
00:14:46,320 --> 00:14:47,530
And that's that.

259
00:14:47,810 --> 00:14:49,120
Have some food.

260
00:14:49,690 --> 00:14:50,580
Meat!

261
00:14:50,580 --> 00:14:52,500
That's raw, you know.

262
00:14:52,500 --> 00:14:54,660
Well, I didn't make it for you!

263
00:14:54,660 --> 00:14:55,390
Tsundere...

264
00:14:55,390 --> 00:14:56,610
Hey, thanks...

265
00:14:56,610 --> 00:14:58,080
Not for you!

266
00:14:58,380 --> 00:15:01,000
It's for that red dog.

267
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:02,540
It's blue. And a cat.

268
00:15:03,350 --> 00:15:07,000
How long until you destroy the moon, huh?

269
00:15:07,370 --> 00:15:09,550
Do I even need to say anything?

270
00:15:09,550 --> 00:15:12,070
Good luck!

271
00:15:12,470 --> 00:15:15,050
I'm beat, and the performance 
hasn't even started...

272
00:15:17,010 --> 00:15:17,930
Then!

273
00:15:19,200 --> 00:15:21,100
It's finally opening day!

274
00:15:24,130 --> 00:15:27,010
I've never had such a large audience!

275
00:15:27,010 --> 00:15:28,610
Thank you very much!

276
00:15:29,230 --> 00:15:33,280
And I never sang in front of so many people!

277
00:15:33,280 --> 00:15:35,120
All that's left is to put on a good show!

278
00:15:43,410 --> 00:15:48,880
Far, far away...

279
00:15:48,880 --> 00:15:54,390
A story of long ago...

280
00:15:54,390 --> 00:16:12,800
A Prince of the West Kingdom fell in love 
with a Princess of a rival Kingdom...

281
00:15:58,980 --> 00:16:01,020
What a beautiful voice!

282
00:16:01,020 --> 00:16:02,770
Wonderful!

283
00:16:10,890 --> 00:16:12,800
Madame!

284
00:16:12,800 --> 00:16:15,180
That Prince is awesome!

285
00:16:13,950 --> 00:16:29,790
To save the Princess, the Prince of the West 
Kingdom went to the mountain of death...

286
00:16:18,950 --> 00:16:20,630
Whoa...

287
00:16:20,630 --> 00:16:22,340
Why is she so nervous?

288
00:16:22,340 --> 00:16:23,950
I guess she's one that 
freezes for the real deal.

289
00:16:23,950 --> 00:16:25,200
Aye!

290
00:16:31,460 --> 00:16:38,520
M-My na... is... Fred... Prin... to save...

291
00:16:38,520 --> 00:16:39,760
What?

292
00:16:39,760 --> 00:16:40,890
But so lovely!

293
00:16:41,210 --> 00:16:42,010
Meat's gone bad!

294
00:16:42,010 --> 00:16:43,300
She's frozen stiff.

295
00:16:43,300 --> 00:16:46,220
No, I can feel the earnest 
nervousness in her performance!

296
00:16:46,220 --> 00:16:48,150
One of those Lamaze method actors, I guess.

297
00:16:48,150 --> 00:16:49,150
Uh, no.

298
00:16:50,240 --> 00:16:53,150
I... With ten swords...

299
00:16:53,150 --> 00:16:54,540
She skipped forward!

300
00:16:54,540 --> 00:16:56,630
It's too early for that line!

301
00:16:56,630 --> 00:16:59,030
She's so nervous, she's barely breathing.

302
00:16:59,330 --> 00:17:02,290
With ten swords of...

303
00:17:07,740 --> 00:17:10,350
More, Madame!

304
00:17:11,300 --> 00:17:13,760
You're risking your life 
just watching this play.

305
00:17:13,760 --> 00:17:14,920
How fun!

306
00:17:14,920 --> 00:17:17,000
Erza's broken down!

307
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:18,470
What are we going to do?

308
00:17:18,470 --> 00:17:22,760
Anyway, we need to try whatever 
we can to cover for her!

309
00:17:22,760 --> 00:17:23,960
Is it my entrance yet?

310
00:17:23,960 --> 00:17:24,730
Shut up!

311
00:17:26,640 --> 00:17:29,660
Oh, please save me, Prince Frederick!

312
00:17:29,660 --> 00:17:33,150
I've been captured by Seinhart!

313
00:17:33,150 --> 00:17:35,430
Seinhart?

314
00:17:35,430 --> 00:17:35,990
Who's that?

315
00:17:36,590 --> 00:17:38,300
My name is Julius!

316
00:17:38,300 --> 00:17:41,620
If you want the Princess back, then fight me!

317
00:17:41,920 --> 00:17:43,440
Who are you?

318
00:17:43,440 --> 00:17:46,020
What happened to Seinhart?

319
00:17:46,020 --> 00:17:47,550
I don't understand!

320
00:17:47,550 --> 00:17:49,120
Everyone is really talented!

321
00:17:49,120 --> 00:17:53,340
F-F-Fight! Fight! Fight!

322
00:17:53,600 --> 00:17:56,170
Crap! Erza's reached her limit!

323
00:17:56,170 --> 00:17:57,460
Leave it to me!

324
00:17:57,460 --> 00:17:59,680
Gate of the Clock, I open thee!

325
00:17:59,680 --> 00:18:01,540
Horologium!

326
00:18:04,850 --> 00:18:09,730
"F-Fight, fight!" she says.

327
00:18:10,360 --> 00:18:12,220
What are you doing, Lucy?

328
00:18:12,220 --> 00:18:16,610
Because if Frederick is defeated 
here, then the story can't progress!

329
00:18:16,910 --> 00:18:19,120
Great Clock, how excellent of you to come!

330
00:18:19,120 --> 00:18:22,360
Please allow Prince Frederick 
to rest a little while!

331
00:18:23,730 --> 00:18:25,360
I've caught my breath!

332
00:18:25,360 --> 00:18:26,810
I'm back!

333
00:18:29,200 --> 00:18:31,920
Take this! Sword of ice!

334
00:18:33,030 --> 00:18:34,570
Why, y-you...

335
00:18:34,570 --> 00:18:38,020
I-I have t-ten swords!

336
00:18:40,060 --> 00:18:41,040
Save me!

337
00:18:41,040 --> 00:18:41,950
Weak!

338
00:18:41,950 --> 00:18:42,840
Don't run!

339
00:18:42,840 --> 00:18:44,560
What realism!

340
00:18:44,560 --> 00:18:46,280
Is this what they call the marriage blues?

341
00:18:46,280 --> 00:18:48,370
How long until he appears?

342
00:18:48,370 --> 00:18:51,260
Thank you very much, Prince Frederick!

343
00:18:52,460 --> 00:18:56,730
P-Princess Yanderica, let us make many children!

344
00:18:56,730 --> 00:18:58,760
About 30 or so!

345
00:18:59,290 --> 00:19:00,670
Isn't that moving a bit fast?

346
00:19:00,670 --> 00:19:02,320
And wait! I don't get it!

347
00:19:02,320 --> 00:19:04,710
But Prince Frederick is dreamy!

348
00:19:02,320 --> 00:19:04,710
This play is surreal...

349
00:19:04,710 --> 00:19:06,410
Pretty interesting.

350
00:19:06,410 --> 00:19:07,790
Everyone is shining!

351
00:19:08,090 --> 00:19:10,750
Your brief respite is now over, thusly!

352
00:19:10,750 --> 00:19:12,530
Julius is back!

353
00:19:12,530 --> 00:19:14,040
What's with the "thusly?"

354
00:19:14,340 --> 00:19:15,880
This is the end for you!

355
00:19:15,880 --> 00:19:18,840
Come, my dragon!

356
00:19:21,640 --> 00:19:24,010
It's finally my cue!

357
00:19:27,640 --> 00:19:29,100
Yes, yes!

358
00:19:30,970 --> 00:19:35,060
I will destroy everything! I am a dragon!

359
00:19:35,360 --> 00:19:36,720
There he is!

360
00:19:36,720 --> 00:19:37,980
The red dog!

361
00:19:39,750 --> 00:19:41,450
In that case, we must join forces!

362
00:19:41,740 --> 00:19:44,360
Y-Yeah... That's quite reassuring.

363
00:19:44,360 --> 00:19:45,770
You're the one that called it!

364
00:19:45,770 --> 00:19:46,910
What kind of a twist is that?

365
00:19:47,210 --> 00:19:49,020
I'll keep it busy!

366
00:19:49,020 --> 00:19:50,360
You two make a run for it!

367
00:19:50,360 --> 00:19:52,490
Princess, what the hell are you doing?

368
00:19:53,320 --> 00:19:54,440
Thanks a bunch!

369
00:19:54,440 --> 00:19:55,010
Yeah!

370
00:19:55,010 --> 00:19:56,500
They're running away?

371
00:19:56,790 --> 00:19:58,710
Ooh, they're eloping!

372
00:19:58,710 --> 00:20:00,730
Gray's one smooth operator.

373
00:20:00,730 --> 00:20:02,010
Oh, youth.

374
00:20:05,420 --> 00:20:06,930
H-Heavy...

375
00:20:16,650 --> 00:20:18,220
Gray, help!

376
00:20:18,220 --> 00:20:20,080
Ice, ice!

377
00:20:18,670 --> 00:20:21,320
All right! Ice Make...

378
00:20:28,840 --> 00:20:29,990
Oh, my...

379
00:20:31,470 --> 00:20:32,950
Thank you very much!

380
00:20:34,130 --> 00:20:36,770
Princess, are you okay?

381
00:20:36,770 --> 00:20:38,980
Why do you hog the spotlight 
when you suck so bad?

382
00:20:38,980 --> 00:20:40,250
Ow!

383
00:20:40,250 --> 00:20:41,460
Ow!

384
00:20:41,460 --> 00:20:43,970
Ow!

385
00:20:43,970 --> 00:20:45,800
Stop it, Natsu!

386
00:20:46,830 --> 00:20:50,410
Princess Yanderica's awesome body is the best!

387
00:20:50,410 --> 00:20:52,410
The best!

388
00:20:52,410 --> 00:20:53,350
Now, now...

389
00:20:53,650 --> 00:20:56,080
What are you doing showing up on your own?

390
00:20:56,080 --> 00:20:58,140
I told you, remember?

391
00:20:58,140 --> 00:21:02,280
I will always protect you 
and your nice body, Lucy!

392
00:21:02,280 --> 00:21:04,450
Why did he even show up?

393
00:21:07,390 --> 00:21:10,850
In this case... I-I must...

394
00:21:10,850 --> 00:21:13,020
...punish you all!

395
00:21:13,360 --> 00:21:15,760
It's all gone to heck!

396
00:21:15,760 --> 00:21:18,920
And... I have a really bad feeling about this...

397
00:21:25,720 --> 00:21:27,590
I knew it!

398
00:21:28,890 --> 00:21:30,780
Why'd it turn out like this?

399
00:21:30,780 --> 00:21:33,450
Macky, hurry up and retire.

400
00:21:33,450 --> 00:21:34,270
Oh, my...

401
00:21:34,270 --> 00:21:36,640
It's the curse of the moon!

402
00:21:42,070 --> 00:21:43,410
Bravo!

403
00:21:43,410 --> 00:21:45,370
Prince Frederick!

404
00:21:49,280 --> 00:21:51,620
Awesome! It was great!

405
00:21:52,940 --> 00:21:54,820
Wonderful!

406
00:22:00,580 --> 00:22:02,620
Then, one week later.

407
00:22:03,750 --> 00:22:06,590
I can't believe it was such a huge hit.

408
00:22:06,930 --> 00:22:10,140
Not bad for a bunch of stand-ins.

409
00:22:10,140 --> 00:22:13,050
Come on, give us our reward already.

410
00:22:13,050 --> 00:22:15,430
Three performances a day is way too much!

411
00:22:15,730 --> 00:22:18,500
Lazy bums! Hurry up and get ready!

412
00:22:18,500 --> 00:22:20,690
He's totally changed...

413
00:22:20,690 --> 00:22:24,940
I want... I want to go home now!

414
00:23:56,260 --> 00:24:01,900
Hey, hey Natsu! I think Llllloke 
totally lllllikes Lllllucy!

415
00:24:01,900 --> 00:24:04,090
Well, if you role your tongue like that...

416
00:24:04,090 --> 00:24:07,500
But seriously, Loke is always avoiding her.

417
00:24:07,500 --> 00:24:10,130
He's just playing hard to get.

418
00:24:10,130 --> 00:24:12,240
Um, sure, whatever you say.

419
00:24:12,240 --> 00:24:13,420
I don't really get it.

420
00:24:13,690 --> 00:24:16,550
Next time: The Star that 
Cannot Return to the Heavens!

421
00:24:16,550 --> 00:24:23,140
Anyway, Llllloke totallllly lllllikes Lllllucy!

422
00:24:23,140 --> 00:24:24,560
You just feel like talking that way, don't you?

